<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8">
    <title>Nosebleed</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="Case_sheet_styles.css">
    <script src="https://www.youtube.com/iframe_api"></script>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="ent General">
      <h3>1ST COMPLAINT: NOSEBLEED (Epistaxis)</h3>
      <!-- S: Site (THE KEY DIFFERENTIATOR) -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Site
          &amp; Laterality</span> <span class="verbal">"Which nostril is the
          bleeding coming from? And does the blood seem to flow from the front
          of your nose, or does it feel like it's dripping down the back of your
          throat?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li><b>ANTERIOR (Front of nose):</b> <span class="ent">Most common,
              usually from Kiesselbach's plexus.</span></li>
          <li><b>POSTERIOR (Back of throat):</b> <b class="ent emergency">More
              serious, often arterial, may not be visible from the front. Red
              Flag.</b></li>
          <li><b>UNILATERAL vs. BILATERAL:</b> Most bleeds are unilateral.
            Bilateral can suggest trauma or a systemic cause.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- O: Onset -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>O</strong>: Onset</span>
        <span class="verbal">"How did it start? Was it spontaneous, or after
          blowing your nose, a knock, or sneezing?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>Spontaneous</li>
          <li>trauma (nose picking, injury, object)</li>
          <li>cold or sinus infection</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- D: Duration -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>D</strong>: Duration</span>
        <span class="verbal">"How long did the bleeding last? And were you able
          to stop it yourself?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="ent emergency">&gt; 15 min despite proper first aid is
            significant.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- A/R: Aggravating / Relieving Factors -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>A/R</strong>:
          Aggravating &amp; Relieving Factors</span> <span class="verbal">"Does
          anything seem to trigger them? What first aid measures did you try?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>AGGRAVATING: </li>
          <ul>
            <li>Dry air, hot environments, nose blowing, alcohol, certain
              medications.</li>
          </ul>
          <li>RELIEVING: </li>
          <ul>
            <li>Pinching the soft part of the nose and leaning forward (correct
              first aid).</li>
          </ul>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- C: Character -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>C</strong>:
          Character</span> <span class="verbal">"Can you describe the bleeding?
          Was it a slow trickle or a heavy, gushing flow? How much blood do you
          think you lost?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>Trickle vs. Profuse flow</li>
          <li>Quantify (e.g., number of soaked tissues, cupfuls)</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- R: Recurrence -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>:
          Recurrence</span> <span class="verbal">"Is this the first time this
          has happened, or are nosebleeds a recurrent problem for you?"</span> </li>
      <!-- A: Associated Symptoms & Risk Factors -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>A</strong>:
          Associated Symptoms &amp; Risks</span> <span class="verbal">"Have you
          noticed any other symptoms, like easy bruising or bleeding from other
          places? And I need to ask about your general health and medications."</span>
        <ul>
          <li><b>LOCAL NASAL SYMPTOMS:</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="ent">Nasal obstruction or blockage (especially if
                one-sided)</li>
              <li class="ent">Facial pain or pressure</li>
              <li class="ent">Reduced sense of smell</li>
              <li class="ent">Nasal crusting</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li><b>CLUES FOR SYSTEMIC BLEEDING DISORDER:</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="hematology">Easy bruising?</li>
              <li class="hematology">Prolonged bleeding from minor cuts or
                dental work?</li>
              <li class="hematology gynob">Heavy menstrual periods?</li>
              <li class="hematology">Bleeding gums?</li>
              <li class="hematology">Family history of bleeding problems (e.g.,
                von Willebrand disease)?</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li><b>RISK FACTORS:</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="pharmacology hematology"><b>Medications:</b>
                Anticoagulants (Warfarin, DOACs), Antiplatelets (Aspirin,
                Clopidogrel), NSAIDs, steroid nasal sprays.</li>
              <li class="cvs"> high blood pressure?</li>
              <li class="git">liver disease (coagulopathy)?</li>
              <li class="psychiatric">Cocaine use?</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- P: Progression -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>:
          Progression</span> <span class="verbal">"Are the nosebleeds becoming
          more frequent or harder to stop?"</span> </li>
      <!-- P: Pattern -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>: Pattern</span>
        <span class="verbal">"Is there any pattern to when they happen?"</span>
      </li>
      <!-- E: Effect on life -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>E</strong>: Effect
          on Life</span> <span class="verbal">"How have these nosebleeds been
          affecting you? Do they cause a lot of anxiety or interfere with your
          activities?"</span> </li>
      <!-- R: Red Flags -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>: Red
          Flags</span> <span class="verbal">"I'm just going to summarize the
          key warning signs I'm looking for."</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="ent emergency"><b>Severe or prolonged </b>(&gt;20-30 mins)
            not stopping with first aid.</li>
          <li class="ent emergency">Suspicion of a <b>posterior bleed</b>
            (bilateral bleeding, or blood flowing into the throat).</li>
          <li class="cvs emergency">hemodynamic compromise (dizziness, fainting,
            extreme pallor).</li>
          <li class="oncology ent emergency">A recurrent unilateral + new nasal
            blockage, facial pain, or neck lump.</li>
          <li class="hematology">Signs of bleeding disorder.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- S: Scale -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Severity
          / Bother Scale</span> <span class="verbal">"On a scale of 1 to 10,
          how severe or worrying are these nosebleeds for you?"</span> </li>
    </div>
    <script src="theme-toggle.js"></script>
    <script src="Iframe_height_mothership.js"></script>
    <script src="Iframe_height.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
